{"id":"337621879_Remarks_about_the_unification_type_of_several_non-symmetric_non-transitive_modal_logics","abstract":"The problem of unification in a normal modal logic $L$ can be defined as follows: given a formula $\\varphi$, determine whether there exists a substitution $\\sigma$ such that $\\sigma (\\varphi )$ is in $L$. In this paper, we prove that for several non-symmetric non-transitive modal logics, there exists unifiable formulas that possess no minimal complete set of unifiers.","authors":["Philippe Balbiani"],"meta":["December 2018Logic Journal of IGPL 27(5)","DOI:10.1093/jigpal/jzy078"],"references":["265644278_Remarks_on_projective_unifiers","220367598_A_Tableau_Method_for_Checking_Rule_Admissibility_in_S4","220245506_Projective_unification_in_modal_logic","220245362_Unification_in_modal_and_description_logics","38355201_Some_Logics_Related_to_von_Wright's_Logic_of_Place","31492449_Unifiability_in_extensions_of_K4","2580899_On_the_Admissible_Rules_of_Intuitionistic_Propositional_Logic","344486660_Modal_Logic","337388248_Elementary_unification_in_modal_logic_KD45","323220429_KD_is_nullary","319567809_Unification_in_epistemic_logics","274151013_Blending_margins_The_modal_logic_K_has_nullary_unification_type","268863827_Unitary_unification_of_S5_modal_logic_and_its_extensions","268863703_Unification_in_common_knowledge_logics","268307289_An_essay_on_unification_and_inference_rules_for_modal_logics","259810779_Modal_Logic","250603261_Bases_of_admissible_rules_of_the_logics_S4_and_Int","250603156_A_criterion_for_admissibility_of_rules_in_the_model_system_S4_and_the_intuitionistic_logic","245215801_Admissibility_of_Logical_Inference_Rules","242640524_Modal_Logic_An_Introduction","226526868_Complexity_of_admissible_rules","222199248_Best_solving_modal_equations","220394664_Unification_in_linear_temporal_logic_LTL","220083012_Construction_of_an_Explicit_Basis_for_Rules_Admissible_in_Modal_System_S4","43075129_Logical_consecutions_in_discrete_linear_temporal_log